# Coding Standards

Use TypeScript strictly.

Prefer:
- Small components
- Clear function names
- Explicit types for important data structures
- Simple state management
- Reusable utilities only when duplication appears

Do not:
- Use `any` unless unavoidable
- Leave unexplained TODOs
- Create dead files
- Duplicate logic across files
- Change unrelated code
- Add dependencies without explaining why

When editing:
1. Modify the smallest set of files.
2. Keep existing style consistent.
3. Update docs if behavior changes.
